g.text: Remember, you and thosearound you could bespreading COVID-19 beforesymptoms appear!
The droplets fly through the air,sometimes traveling more than 12 ft! Thesedroplets can land in eye, mouths, andnoses and be breathed in by thosearound you, spreading COVID-19.
So when you're in a place where you can't consistently keep your distance, it's morelikely that droplets that are produced endup infecting your or those around you.
Since droplets carrythe virus and areprobably the primarymode of spread, tokeep danger low, wemust reduce our exposure to droplets.

For a COVID-19 infection totake hold, an individual needsto be exposed toa certain amount of the virus. This is calledan infectious dose.Researchers aren't sure whatthat dose is yet. However, theinfectious dose is likely verylow.We should do everythingwe can to keep our exposureto the virus as minimal as possible.
